rComments: Tests are nothing like the lectures. Only reason I did somewhat decent in this course was because I learned everything from khan academy and youtube. Spent countless hours on this course as Smith? is clearly not a capable professor. This is a tough course but Smiths incompetence as a professor makes it 10 times harder. Avoid her at all costs!!!!!!!

Horrible Professor, Lectures and assignments have 0 correlation to the questions on the midterms and exams. If you value your GPA avoid smith at all costs. Her excuse for students not doing well in the course was that not enough students attended the additional office hours. As you'll notice most of smiths reviews are 1 star. Worst professor!

Makes the course way harder than necessary and the extremely low class average was a clear representation of this. Retook the course with Dejardins and ended up with an A+. The only course I have failed in my 3 years of engineering at UOttawa. The lectures and assignments are in no way a representation of what is covered on the midterms and exams.

Dr.Smith? is such a nice prof(base what she said) that gives us a lot of questions to do and all the things talk about from lectures have really big difference compared to the midterm and final, sample midterm and final questions help nothing, but at least it gives 1% of idea what gonna be up on the test paper.btw, be ready to see her amazing smile

You will appreciate Smiths? lectures if you are looking to understand the "why" of math concepts. She loves answering questions and is very enthusiastic about teaching math. She goes through examples by hand, which is great. This being said, many examples shown in class are relatively easy compared to the exams. I did not feel prepared for exams.

She's such a good prof omg her lectures were so clear and if she didn't change the grading scheme i would've failed 100% so i love her for that (i got a bad grade cause i didn't pay attention at all lmao)
Tough grader. the first and only D I have ever gotten in my life. Will NEVER take this prof again. AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!!!!!!!!

I really enjoyed this prof and would highly recommend her for anyone thinking of taking her class. She cares about her students and even changes up the marking scheme to give you the best mark possible. Tests were all MC on BS since I had her online, and they reflected the course material. If you practice every day, you will do well in the class.
One of the toughest graders I have ever seen. Worst course I have ever taken up until now.
Great prof! Easy going!

I really hated her at the beginning of the semester cause I got an E on the midterm. However, the final exam is only 12 questions and you get 180 minutes to do it. Straightforward final with a disaster midterm. BUT! SHE GAVE ME AN OPTION OF 100% FINAL AND DRAGGED ME OUT OF HELL. LOVE HER!
Go to class and do the assignments and all the practice problems! Easy A if you actually do the assignment and practice 10 questions per day. No surprises on midterms and finals.

This is my 3rd time taking this course over the last 2.5 decades (guess I just ID-ed myself). Didn't feel any easier but at least I got a solid 'pass' this time around. Spent on average 10+ hours/week on homework. Midterm was more difficult than the final. Tons of practice problems available. Prof was quirky but would take another class with her.

Dr. Smith? made ODE and NM harder than it needs to be. She is a pro in this field, but she doesn't know the threshold of undergraduate students. She turned Laplace transform into a nightmare and make you do very high order numeric methods. The final exam is easier than the midterm. But she is an absolute genius. Very clear in speaking.
Great person. Horrible Professor.

Her explanations are not very good because the calculations seem so basic to her. Also talks very fast and simply shows the calculations on the screen instead of writing anything out. However, she is very nice and is passionate about math. The numerics part of this course is 10x harder than the ODE part. Choose another professor for less stress.
You need to put in the work but if you do, the course is straightforward. There is no bell curve. Lectures are clear and useful.

As a person, I liked Prof. Smith?, but as a teacher, she was pretty unclear and had a tendency to overcomplicate things. TO be completely honest, I had to watch Khan Academy after her lectures which is kind of sad (as we are paying for the lectures, in theory). I am also not sure why we had 7 assignments, that was a bit overkill.
She is a great prof, but the class is harder than the average class. (you need to learn and understand many different ode methods and numerics methods)

The first thing she tells you is that her job is not to teach and I'm assuming it's because she's tenured. that in itself should tell you what kind of prof she is. her course material barely reflects what you get in her assessments and what's supposed to be a straightforward course is the opposite with her. avoid her if you can, for your own sake.

This prof is the hardest marker Ive ever had. The whole class is based off the textbook and they are not invested in helping you succeed at all. Their expectations are not clear whatsoever and the prof is very unprofessional. I will avoid this professor for the rest of my university career.

Stacey Smith? is a very good teacher, she cares about her students and allow a lot of opportunities to improve your grades. practice a lot and you'll do great in this class don't leave all your studying last minute.

Lectures are interesting and she interacts with her students during them. She cares for all students and gives everyone their best chance to get the best mark they can. There was no assigned homework so its all on you to practice outside of class time.

Stacey Smith? really cares about her students and their grades. She gives lots of chances to improve grades and takes time to actually give good answers in class and takes every question seriously. Would recommend her to everyone, even people who suck at math and hate it because she really does make it a little more interesting.

Challenging class, but Dr. Smith? does her utmost to make it understandable and enjoyable. She tries to give students lots of opportunities to succeed. Midterms were difficult, but fair. Do lots of practice and attend the lectures and you should be fine.

Dr. Smith? is one of the most caring profs I've ever had. She genuinely cares about her students' success. She answered every question and was very engaging throughout class time; I definitely felt seen and heard in that class. She also gives practical tips on how to succeed in her class. Do those practice problems and you'll be good.

Dr. Smith? was a really great math prof. She really engaged with students and made math feel relatable to real life. Midterms were tough but she gives you everything you need to succeed. Very fair and understanding. Always there to answer questions and genuinely wants the best for her students.

Professor Dr Stacey Smith? was an amazing prof. She had tons of enthusiasm even at the 8:30 am lectures. She answered all questions thoroughly, gave tons of practice problems and was a very fair marker. She was one of the only profs that cared about improvement throughout the year and gave you chances. However, you have to practice a lot.

Dr. Smith? was such an amazing professor. She really cares about you learning (instead of memorizing formulas). Super inspiring for science students! One thing is that your grades only come from midterms and there was a 60% final, but she tries to make your grade the best it can be. Write in the chat if you're on zoom, she loves the participation!

She's really understanding that understanding the material can happen after the midterm has already passed. She usually gives the option of your next midterm overriding the last one if you do better. Her classes are actually quite fun if you participate as she makes great jokes! One of the better profs I've had!
she really wants you to do well. just come to class and practice like she says. lectures reflect what you'll be tested on. she stays after class and answers EVERY students question.

Don't let his first lecture deceive you, this prof is terrible. Take the class with legit ANYONE else. I like calc and he managed to turn a subject I love into some kind of dreadful mess. His personality is downright inappropriate, very full of himself

It was a pleasure do to the course with professor Smith, even during summer. He's lectures are engaging. He gives many assignments and practice problems which is very useful if you want to have good grades and learn something. He's very calm, patient and he cares a lot about students. He's definitely one of my favorite professors at uOttawa.
He simply does not care about his students. God forbid you submit your work with the wrong title or forget the question mark he added to his name to feel special.

His exam was sooooo long and confusing. How tf do u ask vague questions on a final exam for math wtf. Also hes an extremely hard marker, if you deviate from instructions even slightly you get a 0. Insane stress for a typically stress free course.

The killer who will give you a 0 if you submit the midterm with wrong format of name. Unclear lecture with a lot of contents. Very heavy homework. Extremely difficult exams. If you are expecting a good grade, please never consider about this professor.
Horrible prof, completely intolerant. Seems to enjoy seeing students suffer

Disaster for those student who didnt fill in correctly format of file name. Youll get zero for nothing about the actual exam. Practice exam and suggest problem doesnt help at all. Extremely hard for exam even though he said youll be fine if you do practice. Lier! Talking too fast, terrible lecture performance.

Worst prof Ive ever had. Calls himself a genius, but is a horrible prof. Uses slides to teach math. Sadistic nature. For online courses due to COVID, everyone who didnt name their PDF right got a zero on the final midterm mark which was 30% even though that had nothing to do with the actual exam. Very condescending with students.
Does not tolerate anything. If u submit a file with the wrong name, you get a zero!
I can't find my second page dude. Where is it. Now he changed the question, said there was an error. I can't find it. Help me.

Never had a math prof not do the questions with us. He used slides that you must fill out so by the time you are done trying to copy it down you haven't really understood what was going on. THE ONLY REASON I passed was because of prep 101. He likes to take life science penalties so watch out. Final exam was deadly.. went from an A to a B!

Literally the worst professor I have ever encountered. I usually never write reviews but this guy was surely something. Speaks way too fast and complicates things when they are fairly easy. I respect the amount of knowledge he has but i wish he didnt act as if we knew everything. A lot of mistakes when he tries teaching. Heavily dependent on slides

Leaves you to figure things out on your own. Almost always late and didn't show up most of the first month of classes. During the pandemic he didn't put any effort to teach us. Exams are long and tedious, so if your are not fast at math, forget it. The best advice I can give is, if you want to take science, take it somewhere else.
Not good. Really not good.
Makes material way more complicated than it should be. Big mistake taking this course, wish I listened to the reviews. Better off with another prof. Nice guy tho.

Final was very unpredictable, but he is extremely approachable and genuinely a nice guy. However, during the COVID-19 crisis he was the least accommodating professor I had; the practice questions and material he did post were not very helpful. No matter how much practice is done, most questions are designed to trick you on the exam.

Material isnt difficult and first two midterms fairly represent what was taught. During the pandemic however, minimal material was left to study online and inaccurately represented what was tested. His reassurance that an A+ can be feasibly obtained with the 100% final feels dishonest. Went in with a 94%, final grade took me off the Deans list.

worst experience ever taking a class hands down - prof was looking for things to fail us on for the final and all of us got robbed. Worked way too hard for a mediocre grade in the course. greasy mushroom.

Good guy, but a terrible prof. Although he knows his material, being in his class is very difficult. He speaks too fast, goes through stuff quickly and doesn't give clear explanations. BE PREPARED TO TEACH YOURSELF EVERYTHING. The course is acc very easy if it was taught by a good prof, but with a prof who can't explain and teach makes it hard.

Talks way to fast, rarely ever clearly conveys a topic, exams are too long especially after switching to online classes halfway through the course due to pandemic. If youre not that great at math and have this prof I would highly recommend you get a tutor as you will be doing most of the teaching yourself anyways. 11/10 would not take again.

This was by far my least favourite class usually love mathematics however his teaching strategies are extremely dated and you will be in constant confusion as he doesnt give course updates until last second. Talks way to fast in lectures and is horrible at explaining. Highly recommend avoiding his class at all cost.

WORST PROF I HAVE EVER HAD! Goes too fast in class you don't even know whats going on and you need to go to copy his notes. If you have him, you're pretty much teaching the whole course, and IMO you really do need to work from calc 1. There is a HUGE jump. Half is linear (easy) and half is integrals (hard). If you have a good prof you'll be good.
He is a horrible prof. End of Story.

The professor does not make the mobius consistent, he makes it due a random day rather than making it consistent and not announcing when it is due. In addition, this prof never is organized when teaching the lectures, they are all over the place and excepts us to understand the lectures even tho the assignments do not cover that subject.
Exams leave you pressed for time and are usually only out of 30 with some questions being worth upwards of 6 marks each

He is one of the best teachers I have ever taken. I would take his class again. all you need is to practice on your own and you will guarantee the A+ mark. He is not hard but do not miss any class, missing one class will cause you a real mess.

He is a solid prof. His lectures are pretty good, and while they can be a bit all over the place and confusing at times, if you ask him any question at his office hours he is SUPER helpful. You have to work in his class, but if you do you'll do very well!

What was supposed to be an easy class turned out to be the most difficult I've ever taken. Terrible explanations,  and I've never been graded more UNFAIRLY in a math class as I was by his TA. Class avg was 30, weekly assignments were impossible. In the end the final had to be easy or else no one would pass. It was also 100% of our mark.
Probably the hardest section, his lecture is very confusing. However he is available outside class, so prepared to spend 5 hours a day doing practice problem if you want to get a good mark.

During classes he just wasted our time by making us copy solutions from the board even though he ends up posting the solutions on blackboard at the end of the semester. He never actually solves problems in class, just mumbles vague unhelpful explanations.  Assignments and exams are tough and grading is even tougher. Take this course w another prof
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: There's assignments every week which are brutally hard and extremely time-consuming, he claimed the midterm was going to be easier but it was just as hard.  This prof wants you to spend a ridiculous amount of time learning the concepts.  Don't waste your time, take this course with a different prof.

Great prof  and his in-class notes really do help understand the various concpets. Everyone who scares you from the zombie stuff don't believe them; literally only two equations does he bring it up for examples. The man is passionate about zombies! Give him a break! Midterms are fair but exam was tough. Do examples and you'll be fine:)

His explanations were vague, unhelpful and there was really no point in going to class. The class average on the midterm was 30% which shows how bad he was at teaching this course. Final exam wasn't any better either. Be smart and choose another prof.

He talks fast and has the amazing ability of complicating simple ideas. And the book he wrote does not provide you clear and step-by-step explanations. Found an alternative textbook to teach myself the materials.

He is a bad prof as you can judge from his name, half of the time I had no clue what was he talking about. He focuses on a lot of unimportant material and makes so many mistakes in class. Moreover, his faculty approved calculator thing is no joke. Bring the faculty approved calculator to his exam otherwise he will confiscate yours!!!

His exams are definitely tough, and so is his marking scheme. The course itself also has some challenging material, and you have to have a firm grasp of the concepts in order to pass the exams. However, he is very helpful and approachable during office hours, and if you put in some effort, you can definitely get an A.

He made ODE's which should be straight forward, incredibly confusing.  His fill in the blank notes stopped me learning properly, he cannot teach off of a chalk board and therefore was useless. He made my semester 20 times harder than it needed to be. Unless you're naturally a genius at math, don't take him. Desjardins all the way!

Assignments are rough and don't reflect examples gone over in class. He left 2 weeks before the second midterm, which was deadly (I thought I understood what was going on..). If you can have another prof, take them! He goes off on tangents about zombies and diseases and loses the students' attention and interest very easily. Not happy.

His ODE notes are way too convoluted (or "complete"), and he makes the class much more difficult than need be. ODE is fairly straightforward but he feels all over the place. Also, his communication about expectations, midterms, etc. is poor and nonexistent on Blackboard.  Take the class with Desjardins and you'll be fine.

Spends more time on talking about diseases and how students need to think about each step on tests than he does actually teaching any math. His fill in the blanks approach is horrid for teaching ODE. Spends too much time on unimportant content.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Ordinary differential equation is a relatively easy course but I wouldn't recommend taking it with professor smith if you don't know what you are doing. His notes are complete and has a decent job of explaining it word by word but he speaks too damn fast during lectures
Classes are extremely boring and he goes off on random tangents a lot. If there's an option for another professor I'd suggest choosing them over Smith.

I found this to be a pretty easy course. I barely used to textbook. He provides good notes (even though there are some typos). Also, the weekly assignments were more than enough practice for me and I didn't need to do extra Qs from the textbook. His exams are good. They cover the material covered in class & assignments. I would recommend Dr. Smith

A really good prof. I find he was the best prof for calculus life science 1... I regretted not having him for sem 2. Although the zombie thing is just plain weird and immature. His notes are awesome and he is really helpful in office hours... Got an A+ and I didn't really work for it. MASTER THE ASSIGNMENTS! Do them 10 times and u will nail exams

Gives out his notes in a package - makes it easier to follow him when he's teaching. May talk quickly at times but is very nice, helpful and cares for his students. Midterm/FSM/Exam are easy if you have gone through his notes thoroughly. Assignments can be tough at times but help understand the content well. DGDs are useless. Recommend this prof!

He was good, but I felt like he didn't prepare us enough for the midterms and finals compared to other profs; even though i got 96% on the midterm. The profs actually make the tests together; so the more yr prof prepares you the better you do. He's nice and approachable during office hours!!! and funny sometimes

Very enthusiastic about math and zombies. If you took calculus before, the course material is easy. He doesn't always explain everything and he only remembers stuff when someone asks him. He also goes off on tangents a lot (he's had one on tangent). He is helpful though! Oh and don't buy the textbook unless you plan to go to the very bad DGDs.

Funny Australian man!! Pleasure to have him. He was easy to understand and great at teaching. 80% of the course was the easy grade 12 material... i dont see why people are complaining how hard it was. exams and midterms are expected like he said. Just study the assignments and attend the DGDs ended with 100 in the course.

Smith appears to know the material well, but half the time had trouble explaining it. He would go off on a concept, and then come back to the original one, and would spend lots of time trying to fix his examples because they weren't working, which was very time consuming and confusing.
Great guy. easy course. 3/4 of the course WAS Gr 12 calc. Enthusiastic about zombies and disease. great humour. Easy to follow/understand if you actually cared to listen and understand gr12 calc.

Good prof, but talks a little fast. He makes the first part of the course super easy if you took grade 12 calc. He's helpful and has a good sense of humour, but his final exam was brutal. You usually need to read up on the textbook to understand any of his notes.
Smith? actually made calculus very interesting with zombies and diseases. He talks a little fast though.

Obsessed with zombies, but that's pretty cool. Can talk really fast sometimes but he is a great prof, easy to do well in his class if you know what you're doing and follow along in class. DGD's really help for this one.

Pretty hilarious guy although he talks too fast and is hard to understand on the spot. You will definitely need to review your notes after class if you want to understand anything at all. Midterms and final were fair, but the marking is ludicrous. Each question is worth only 3-6 points, yet you get full marks removed for the smallest errors. Unfair

Smith? is a great prof hands down. He is always willing to help and has a good sense of humor. Although some of the material is sometimes dry, he tries to make it interesting with neat examples and presentations. He's very fair when it comes to assessments as he wants his students to succeed, and you will if you put in the work. Great prof.
A good prof. Can talk REALLY fast sometimes. His writing can sometimes be illegible. Notes are good. Has some sense of humour. Material in lectures is relatively easy to understand.
He's hilarious - Math profs with a good sense of humour is refreshing! One of my favourites! (AND you actually use the text book you pay for!!)
best math prof i had. willing to help outside of class hours.

At first he was clear, and went through material very well.  Farther into the course he started to do examples that didn't make sense, answering problems in ways that are not necessary, and went off tangent.  Sometimes he's clear, mostly not.
Prof. Smith? is nice, and his lectures are pretty good. I understand concepts and examples in class, and I find his website to be amusing. :)
Hey rocks!

Races through lectures at the speed of light. Consistently cancels example questions near the end after spending 15 minutes on them because it didn't work. Leans over the overhead projector and covers up what he's writing. VERY nice guy, but seemed quite shy and nervous and just wasn't that helpful for a course like this.
His accent can be hard to understand at times, and usually his voice causes feedback, which is really annoying. He seems organized, but he doesn't explain things in a way that people will understand
No Comments
